## Example 5 — Composite Figure Area

A figure consists of a rectangle (12 m × 8 m) with a triangle (base 12 m, height 5 m) on top. Find the total area.

### Step 1: Find the Area of the Rectangle

$$A_{\text{rect}} = 12 \times 8 = 96 \text{ m}^2$$

### Step 2: Find the Area of the Triangle

$$A_{\text{tri}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 12 \times 5 = 30 \text{ m}^2$$

### Step 3: Add the Areas

$$A_{\text{total}} = 96 + 30 = 126 \text{ m}^2$$

✅ Answer: The total area is **126 m²**.

